        <h2 class="heading-3">phase three</h2>
        <h1 class="heading-5">2016 - 2019</h1>
        <div class="div-block-9">
          <p class="paragraph">With <strong>eleven</strong> movies, <strong>Phase Three</strong> of the <strong class="bold-text">Marvel Cinematic Universe </strong>is by far the most <strong>ambitious</strong> and concludes the <strong>Infinity Saga.</strong><br><br>Most of the <strong>initial Avengers</strong> are still central to the story. Even with no <strong>Iron Man</strong> movie, <strong>Tony Stark </strong><em>(Robert Downey Jr.)</em> still plays a significant <em>(if not the biggest) </em>role alongside <strong>Steve Rogers</strong> <em>(Chris Evans)</em>, <strong>Thor</strong> <em>(Chris Hemsworth)</em>, <strong>Bruce Banner</strong> <em>(Mark Ruffalo)</em>, and <strong>Natasha Romanoff</strong> <em>(Scarlett Johansson)</em>.<br><br>Of course, it is impossible not to mention <strong>Thanos </strong><em>(Josh Brolin), </em>who appears in only <strong>two</strong> movies but <strong>ties </strong>all of the Infinity Saga <strong>together </strong>with the <strong>Infinity Stones</strong>.<br>‍<br><strong>Phase Three</strong> also introduces <strong>new</strong> crucial Marvel characters like <strong>Spider-Man</strong> <em>(Tom Holland)</em>, <strong>Doctor Strange</strong> <em>(Benedict Cumberbatch)</em>, <strong>Black Panther</strong> <em>(Chadwick Boseman)</em>, and <strong>Captain Marvel</strong> <em>(Brie Larson).</em><br><br>The movies cumulated <strong>$13.5 billion</strong> at the global box office. <strong>Avengers: Infinity War</strong> is the fifth, and <strong>Avengers: Endgame</strong> is the second of the <strong>highest-grossing films ever. </strong><br></p>
